# Bug Fix Verification Checklist

## Before Starting

- [ ] Understand the bug report — reproduce the issue locally
- [ ] Identify root cause through code exploration (not just symptoms)
- [ ] Check if there's a related issue/ticket to reference

## Implementation

- [ ] Address the root cause, not just symptoms
- [ ] Keep changes minimal and focused on the fix
- [ ] Follow the CE-EE pattern if the fix touches extensible components
- [ ] No hardcoded values, no debug logging (`console.log`, `System.out.println`)
- [ ] Use safe property access (optional chaining or lodash/get for deeply nested objects)
- [ ] Handle edge cases and null/undefined gracefully

## Testing

- [ ] Write a test that reproduces the bug before fixing (confirms the fix actually works)
- [ ] Verify related functionality isn't broken (regression check)
- [ ] Test both CE and EE paths if the fix touches feature-flagged code
- [ ] Server: run the test class — `cd app/server && source envs/test.env.example && mvn test -pl appsmith-server -Dtest=ClassName`
- [ ] Client: run relevant tests — `cd app/client && yarn test:unit`

## Before Committing

- [ ] Server changes: `mvn spotless:apply` runs automatically via Husky pre-commit
- [ ] Client changes: `eslint --fix` + `prettier --write` runs automatically via Husky pre-commit
- [ ] PR title follows Conventional Commits: `fix(scope): description`
- [ ] Reference the issue/ticket in PR description
